This paper deals with auctions and mechanisms, which are topics in game theory and algorithmic economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of mechanisms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses revenue optimization, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
